    • deviceEnabled

      public void deviceEnabled(boolean enable) throws jpos.JposException
      Beschreibung aus Schnittstelle kopiert: JposBaseInterface
      Final part of setting DeviceEnabled. Can be overwritten within derived classes. Performs initOnEnable method of corresponding property set in addition to setting DeviceEnabled. This method will be called only if the following plausibility checks lead to a positive result:
      • Device has not been closed,
      • ExclusiveUse equals ExclusiveYes: Device is claimed,
      • DeviceEnabled != enabled.

    • waitForDrawerClose

      public void waitForDrawerClose() throws jpos.JposException
      Beschreibung aus Schnittstelle kopiert: CashDrawerInterface
      Final part of WaitForDrawerClose method. Can be overwritten in derived class, if necessary. The parameters beepTimeout, beepDuration, beepFrequency and beepDelay will not be used by this method because beeping will be performed directly by the service. This method will be called only if the following plausibility checks lead to a positive result:
      • Device is enabled,
      • CapStatus is true,
      • The parameters beepTimeout, beepDuration and beepDelay of the calling method are positive or FOREVER,
      • The parameter beepFrequency is between 10 and 24000.
      If the deprecated waitForDrawerClose method (which must handle beeping itself) shall be used, this method must throw a JposException with ErrorCode = 0.
      Angegeben von:
      waitForDrawerClose in Schnittstelle CashDrawerInterface
      Setzt außer Kraft:
      waitForDrawerClose in Klasse CashDrawerProperties
      Löst aus:
      jpos.JposException - If an error occurs.
